{"name":"READ ME! - Ouija Board","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.ouija-board-for-sequencer.journal-ouija-board.bMbNhHdH69CkEuYJ"}},"pages":[{"name":"How To Use Your Own Image","type":"text","_id":"SC3DZ2EgkTiqpsBd","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>How To Use Your Own Image</h1><p>You can use your own ouija board image and ouija pointer.</p><p> The only work you'll have is to map the position of the pointer to the letter or symbol in the ouija board.</p><p></p><h2>How to Map</h2><p>1. Find the macro <strong>Get Token XY</strong> in your world. @UUID[Macro.MuCKWfictihftquC]{Get Token XY}</p><img src=\"modules/ouija-board-for-sequencer/assets/guide/bottomlocation.webp\" width=\"700\" height=\"415\" /><p>2. Find a position in the bottom of the image. This point is very important. All movement will look for it.</p><p>3. Move the ouija pointer to the desired position.</p><p>4. Run the macro Get Token XY.</p><img src=\"modules/ouija-board-for-sequencer/assets/guide/pointermap.webp\" width=\"480\" height=\"474\" /><p>5. You need to paste the positions into the macro Ouija Board Control. Make a backup of it and paste the position at:</p><blockquote><p>map.bottomLocation = <strong>{ x: 607.1601354620223, y: 785.2926947266571 }</strong>;</p></blockquote><p>6. Now, move the pointer to a letter/number. If you have trouble to position the token hold shift to move with precision. Run the macro to get the position and paste it in the right location.</p><blockquote><p>// ---------------------------</p><p>// MAP</p><p>map.letter_a = { x: 231.1892510005717, y: 445.45454545454555 };</p><p>map.letter_b = { x: 292.1097770154374, y: 404.8885077186964 };</p><p>map.letter_c = { x: 349.28530588907967, y: 379.0451686678102 };</p><p>map.letter_d = { x: 404.3739279588336, y: 361.1206403659233 };</p><p>map.letter_e = { x: 461.7209834190966, y: 348.8564894225272 };</p><p>map.letter_f = { x: 514.9228130360204, y: 336.79245283018867 };</p><p>map.letter_g = { x: 577.1869639794168, y: 333.96226415094344 };</p><p>map.letter_h = { x: 637.9073756432248, y: 333.01886792452837 };</p><p>map.letter_i = { x: 691.1092052601487, y: 334.9056603773585 };</p><p>map.letter_j = { x: 738.8507718696399, y: 340.3659233847914 };</p><p>map.letter_k = { x: 801.2864493996568, y: 353.94511149228146 };</p></blockquote><p>After you paste one letter, run the macro Ouija Board Control to see if the position is ok. If not, run the macro to get the position and paste it again.</p><p> </p><h1>Create an Actor</h1><p>1. Create an actor (any type). Set the <strong>prototype token</strong> as the image. </p><img src=\"modules/ouija-board-for-sequencer/assets/guide/tokenconfig.webp\" /><p>2. Move this actor to your scene.</p><p></p><h2>Notes</h2><ul><li><p>You have six custom positions (symbol_01, symbol_02, etc). You can use this to whatever you want. </p></li><li><p>If you messed up the macros, just import them again. It's easier if you make a duplicate of the macros before change them.</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Move Types","type":"text","_id":"j20GDcDmSjO5XCmr","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Move Types</h2><p> </p><ul><li><p>Move 1 - Standard: Move and play a sound.</p></li><li><p>Move 2 -  No Sound/No Animation: Just move.</p></li><li><p>Move 3 - Animation at the End: Move and play an animation at the end. Play scary sound.</p></li></ul><p></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"How To Use Ouija Board","type":"text","_id":"B8YtxgWFcsn79qLg","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>Instructions </h1><p>1. Import the scene (Ouija Board) into your world. @UUID[Compendium.ouija-board-for-sequencer.scene-ouija-board.3c6cvZdkrf7UcSMu]{Ouija Board}</p><p>2. Import the macro <strong>Ouija Board Control</strong>. @UUID[Compendium.ouija-board-for-sequencer.macros-ouija-board.3TvObpeOAdbRgDY8]{Ouija Board Control}</p><p>3. Select the <strong>Ouija Pointer Token</strong> and run the macro. You can type a message. Move to Yes/No. You can set some custom positions. </p><p>You can change the movement type. Delay Min/Max let you add an extra time before the next movement. Example: Delay Min: 500 and Delay Max: 1500 will add a delay between the next movement within the range of 0,5 seconds to 1,5 seconds. This looks less mechanical.</p><img src=\"modules/ouija-board-for-sequencer/assets/guide/macro.webp\" /><p> </p><h2>Notes</h2><ul><li>If you type space, it will move to an \"space\" position</li><li>This scene has only one extra position. Custom Position 2-6 can be use for your custom image.</li><li>If you type the same letter/position in a roll the pointer will jiggle. Example: died in the p<strong>oo</strong>l. It'll jiggle in the <strong>oo</strong>.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"KD4HGobhPLq6jmnP":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldbuilding","systemVersion":"0.7.1","coreVersion":"10.285","createdTime":1662389507073,"modifiedTime":1663506391393,"lastModifiedBy":"xoZUVVkfSPCLleuq"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"PdIcUhbKdGWmVOvt"}
